    "body": "- `nvim --version`: `NVIM v0.4.3`\r\n- `vim -u DEFAULTS` (version: 8.0) behaves differently? This issue need a vimrc to be reproduced. \r\n- Operating system/version:`Linux 5.3.0-40-generic #32~18.04.1-Ubuntu SMP Mon Feb 3 14:05:59 UTC 2020 x86_64`\r\n- Terminal name/version: `Gnome terminal 3.28.2`\r\n- `$TERM`: `xterm-256color`\r\n\r\n### This is the vimrc that I am using to cause this problem. Save it a s 'minimal'\r\n```\r\nset nocompatible\r\n\r\nfunction! DoEcho()\r\n\tsilent !ls\r\n\techo \"llll\"\r\nendfunction\r\n\r\nnnoremap <silent> p :call DoEcho()<CR>\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce using `nvim -u minimal`\r\n\r\nPress p\r\n\r\n### Actual behaviour\r\nAfter pressing p notice that you see a blank line the message that was echo'd and a prompt at the bottom of the screen.\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nllll\r\nPress ENTER or type command to continue\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\nJust the echo'd message should be seen\r\n```\r\nllll\r\n```\r\n\r\nVim version 8.0 only displays the echo'd message.\r\n\r\n### Note\r\nThis only seems to happen when echo is called after running external commands, otherwise it behaves as expected.",
